<section class="slide energy-slide"
         data-section="Background"
         data-title="ILP as a factorized energy model">

  <div class="slide-body energy-body">

    <div class="energy-layout">

      <div class="energy-formula-panel">
        <div class="energy-formula">

          <div class="energy-kicker">Binary ILP</div>

          <div class="energy-block">
            \[
            \max_{x \in \{0,1\}^n} c^\top x
            \quad \text{s.t.} \quad Ax \leq b
            \]
          </div>

          <div class="fragment energy-arrow" data-fragment-index="1">
            \[
            \Downarrow
            \]
          </div>

          <div class="fragment energy-block" data-fragment-index="1">
            \[
            E(x)
            =
            -c^\top x
            +
            \sum_{a=1}^{m}
            \mathbf{1}[A_a x \leq b_a]
            \]
          </div>

          <div class="fragment energy-indicator" data-fragment-index="2">
            \[
            \mathbf{1}[A_a x \leq b_a]
            =
            \begin{cases}
            0, & A_a x \leq b_a,\\
            +\infty, & \text{otherwise}.
            \end{cases}
            \]
          </div>

        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="energy-graph-panel">

        <svg class="energy-svg" viewBox="0 0 620 430" role="img"
             aria-label="Factorized energy model induced by an ILP">

          <!-- objective contribution -->
          <g class="fragment" data-fragment-index="1">
            <rect class="energy-objective-box" x="65" y="45" width="180" height="62" rx="18"></rect>
            <text class="energy-objective-text" x="155" y="84">
              objective
            </text>
            <text class="energy-objective-formula" x="155" y="125">
              −cᵀx
            </text>
          </g>

          <!-- variable nodes -->
          <g class="fragment" data-fragment-index="1">
            <g class="energy-var-node" transform="translate(170 190)">
              <circle r="34"></circle>
              <text y="8">x₁</text>
            </g>

            <g class="energy-var-node" transform="translate(170 285)">
              <circle r="34"></circle>
              <text y="8">x₂</text>
            </g>

            <g class="energy-var-node" transform="translate(170 380)">
              <circle r="34"></circle>
              <text y="8">x₃</text>
            </g>
          </g>

          <!-- factor nodes -->
          <g class="fragment" data-fragment-index="3">
            <g class="energy-factor-node" transform="translate(450 190)">
              <rect x="-58" y="-30" width="116" height="60" rx="16"></rect>
              <text y="7">E₁</text>
            </g>

            <g class="energy-factor-node" transform="translate(450 285)">
              <rect x="-58" y="-30" width="116" height="60" rx="16"></rect>
              <text y="7">E₂</text>
            </g>

            <g class="energy-factor-node" transform="translate(450 380)">
              <rect x="-58" y="-30" width="116" height="60" rx="16"></rect>
              <text y="7">E₃</text>
            </g>
          </g>

          <!-- edges -->
          <g class="fragment" data-fragment-index="4">
            <line class="energy-edge" x1="170" y1="190" x2="450" y2="190" />
            <line class="energy-edge" x1="170" y1="285" x2="450" y2="190" />

            <line class="energy-edge" x1="170" y1="190" x2="450" y2="285" />
            <line class="energy-edge" x1="170" y1="285" x2="450" y2="285" />
            <line class="energy-edge" x1="170" y1="380" x2="450" y2="285" />

            <line class="energy-edge" x1="170" y1="285" x2="450" y2="380" />
            <line class="energy-edge" x1="170" y1="380" x2="450" y2="380" />
          </g>

          <text class="energy-side-label fragment" data-fragment-index="1" x="170" y="150">
            variables
          </text>

          <text class="energy-side-label fragment" data-fragment-index="3" x="450" y="150">
            constraint energies
          </text>

          <text class="energy-caption fragment" data-fragment-index="4" x="310" y="32">
            each row of A becomes one local energy term
          </text>

        </svg>

      </div>

      <div class="energy-mrf-bridge fragment" data-fragment-index="5">
        <span class="energy-bridge-prefix">Next:</span>
        this factorized energy defines a graphical model over solutions
        <span class="energy-bridge-arrow">→</span>
        <strong>Markov random fields</strong>
      </div>

    </div>

    <aside class="notes">
      Before introducing Markov random fields formally, this slide shows that a binary
      ILP can already be interpreted as an energy model over assignments. The objective
      contributes a global linear score, while each constraint row contributes a local
      extended-valued energy: zero when the row is satisfied and infinity otherwise.
      This gives a natural factorization along the constraint nodes of the bipartite graph.
    </aside>

  </div>
</section>
